From 6034b52126bd45d3534c479ffc1981e9fb6a2b82 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 01:23:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add Purchasing department, vendor part tracking
 foundation

Schema:
- New PartSourceType enum (Fabricated | Vendor) on PartType - vendor
  parts don't go through process routing at all, just received/pending
  tracking, so this needed to be a genuinely separate concept from the
  existing fabricated-part-type + route model, not a variant of it.
- New VendorPart model: unitId, partTypeId, isReceived, expectedArrivalDate,
  receivedDate, addedByUserId. Dates stay editable regardless of
  received status, since arrival dates slip.
- Unit gets assignedTeamName + assemblyStartedAt for the "Start Building
  Unit" action (separate from manufacturingStartedAt, which is
  Fabrication's kickoff moment via startManufacturing() - a different
  event entirely from Assembly starting its own build).
- Purchasing department seeded - toggle on/off using the isActive field
  every department already has, no new toggle mechanism needed.
- 5 seed vendor part types: HX Coil, DX Coil, Fan, Motor, Heat Exchanger.
- New vendor-part:manage permission; new "Purchasing" role; Supervisor
  and Planner roles both also granted vendor-part:manage (Supervisor
  needs it for when Purchasing is toggled off and Assembly has to
  self-serve; Planner per "vendor parts...that planner has manually put
  in it").

Backend:
- New VendorPartsModule: GET/POST /units/:unitId/vendor-parts,
  PATCH/DELETE /vendor-parts/:id.
- PartTypesService/Controller: sourceType now settable on create/update,
  filterable via ?sourceType= on GET /part-types.
- New POST /units/:id/start-assembly (task:start), captures teamName.
- New GET /units/assembly-summary: Upcoming/WIP unit lists for Assembly,
  each unit including both its Fabrication Parts and its VendorParts.

Frontend:
- Part Types config page: added the missing Source (Fabricated/Vendor)
  field - previously there was no way to actually create a new vendor
  part type beyond the 5 seeded ones.
