From 07dec4d0474cc0dadad820cbd06ea36c633f1bdc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 01:24:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Purchasing Dashboard, and Assembly's Upcoming/WIP view
 with Start Building Unit

Purchasing Dashboard (/purchasing-dashboard): drag a vendor part type
from the palette onto a unit card - opens a modal asking if it's
received (Yes/No), then the appropriate date (expected arrival if not
received, actual receipt date if it is). Existing vendor parts on a
unit show as small received/pending badges; clicking one reopens the
same modal in edit mode, since arrival dates need to stay editable
after the fact.

Supervisor Dashboard now branches on Assembly specifically: instead of
the generic station-grouped task board, Assembly sees two headed
sections - "WIP" (units where Assembly has actually started building,
with progress) and "Upcoming Units" (in production, Assembly hasn't
started yet). Every unit card in both sections shows its Fabrication
parts and vendor parts (received/pending) as small chips, so Assembly
can see what's actually arrived at a glance without opening the unit.

"Start Building Unit" (Upcoming section only) opens a modal that:
- Shows the vendor-parts checklist for that unit so Assembly can
  actually check status before starting, per the requirement
- If Purchasing is toggled off (checked via the Purchasing department's
  isActive flag), shows an inline "log what's needed" section instead -
  quick-add buttons per vendor part type, added as not-received with no
  date, editable later from the unit's own page
- Requires a team name, calls POST /units/:id/start-assembly on submit

Also added Purchasing to the sidebar nav, gated on vendor-part:manage.
